11 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
12 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
13 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 14-127 of Title 47, unless there
14 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
15 The Department of Transportation is authorized to increase any
16 oversize- or overweight-related permit fees found in its
17 administrative rules including, but not limited to:
18 1. Special Over-height Trailer Permit for Limited Travel
19 thirty-day (30-day) permit;
20 2. Longer Combination Vehicle Annual Permit; and
21 3. Special Over-height Trailer Permit for Limited Travel Annual
22 Permit.
23 The Department shall use a formula for calculating the changes
24 to the fees using a cost-of-living adjustment through the year 2024.
Req. No. 3939 Page 2

1 When collecting the fees authorized under the provisions of this
2 section, the Department shall deposit the amount of the difference
3 between the fees as of the effective date of this act and the
4 increased fees authorized by this section to the credit of the
5 Rebuilding Oklahoma Access and Driver Safety Fund.
6 SECTION 2. AMENDATORY 47 O.S. 2021, Section 14-103, as
7 amended by Section 3, Chapter 116, O.S.L. 2022 (47 O.S. Supp. 2025,
8 Section 14-103), is amended to read as follows:
9 Section 14-103. A. Except as otherwise provided for by this
10 chapter, no vehicle, with or without load, shall have a total
11 outside width in excess of one hundred two (102) inches excluding:
12 1. Tire bulge;
13 2. Approved safety devices;
14 3. A retracted awning with a width of eight (8) inches or less
15 or other appurtenance of four (4) inches or less which is attached
16 to the side of a recreational vehicle, as defined in Section 1102 of
17 this title; and
18 4. Pins used as a safety precaution or as a load-assisting
19 device if the pins do not extend the overall width of the vehicle
20 beyond nine (9) feet. The State of Oklahoma hereby declares it has
21 determined, in accordance with 23 C.F.R., Section 658.15, that such
22 pins are necessary for the safe and efficient operation of motor
23 vehicles.
24
Req. No. 3939 Page 3

1 The provisions of this subsection shall not apply to any person
2 engaged in the hauling of round baled hay with a total outside width
3 of eleven (11) feet or less when the hay is owned by such person and
4 is being hauled for any purpose other than resale. The provisions
5 of this subsection shall also not apply to any county official or
6 employee engaged in the hauling or pulling of a trailer or equipment
7 owned by the county on the county roads of such county.
8 B. Except as otherwise provided for by this chapter:
9 1. No vehicle, with or without load, shall exceed a height of
10 thirteen and one-half (13 1/2) feet on any county road, or fourteen
11 (14) feet on any turnpike, interstate, U.S. or state highway, unless
12 a greater height is authorized by a special permit issued by the
13 Executive Director of the Department of Transportation or an
14 authorized representative of the Department of Transportation
15 specifying the highways to be used, consistent with public
16 convenience and safety. The prohibitions on movement as prescribed
17 in subsection F of Section 14-101 of this title and paragraph 1 of
18 subsection G of Section 14-101 of this title shall not apply to
19 vehicles operated pursuant to such permits;
20 2. An official state bridge vertical clearance map providing
21 clearance heights as posted for bridges on the interstate, U.S. and
22 state highway systems shall be available on the Oklahoma Department
23 of Transportation website; and
24
